--- a/models/graph_service.py
+++ b/models/graph_service.py
@@ Description:
@  Auto-trigger RAG enrichment on top match results after Stage 2
@  scoring completes.  Fires inside persist_two_stage_results() so
@  every two-stage run gets RAG context without manual button clicks.
@
@  Safe: checks module installed, catches all exceptions, never
@  blocks the match pipeline.  RAG is best-effort enrichment.
@
@ Target method: persist_two_stage_results(self, intake, results)
@ Insert point: AFTER the for-loop that creates match.result records,
@               BEFORE the return statement.
@
@ Depends: plasticos_kb_rag module installed (graceful skip if not)

================================================================================
PATCH D — Auto RAG Enrichment Hook
================================================================================

In graph_service.py, locate the method:

    def persist_two_stage_results(self, intake, results):

Find the END of the method, just before the final return.  You'll see
something like:

        ...
        return rows

Insert the following block BEFORE that return:

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INSERT THIS (before `return rows` or `return merged_results`):
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

        # ── AUTO RAG ENRICHMENT (Patch D) ──────────────────────────────
        # Best-effort: enrich top match results with KB context.
        # Skips gracefully if plasticos_kb_rag is not installed.
        try:
            if "plasticos.match.result" in self.env:
                MatchResult = self.env["plasticos.match.result"].sudo()
                # Check if RAG module is installed (rag_insight field exists)
                if "rag_insight" in MatchResult.fields_get():
                    top_n = int(
                        self.env["ir.config_parameter"].sudo().get_param(
                            "plasticos.rag.auto_enrich_top_n", "5"
                        )
                    )
                    top_results = MatchResult.search(
                        [("intake_id", "=", intake.id)],
                        order="score desc",
                        limit=top_n,
                    )
                    if top_results:
                        top_results.action_rag_enrich()
                        _logger.info(
                            "Auto RAG enrichment: %d results enriched "
                            "for intake %s",
                            len(top_results),
                            intake.name,
                        )
        except Exception as exc:
            # NEVER block the match pipeline for RAG failures
            _logger.warning(
                "Auto RAG enrichment skipped (non-fatal): %s", exc
            )
        # ── END PATCH D ────────────────────────────────────────────────

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ALSO ADD this system parameter (optional, controls batch size):
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

In Settings → Technical → System Parameters, add:

    Key:   plasticos.rag.auto_enrich_top_n
    Value: 5

This controls how many top results get auto-enriched per intake run.
Default is 5 if the parameter doesn't exist.

================================================================================
VERIFICATION:
================================================================================

After applying, trigger a match run:

    intake.action_find_buyers()

Check the top 5 match.result records — they should have:
  - rag_enrichment_date  populated
  - rag_chunk_count      > 0  (if KB chunks exist)
  - rag_insight          non-empty
  - Chatter note         "🧠 RAG Enrichment Complete"

If plasticos_kb_rag is NOT installed, the patch does nothing (safe skip).
If no KB chunks exist yet, each result gets a chatter warning instead.

================================================================================
ALSO APPLICABLE TO: match_buyers_for_intake() (single-stage legacy path)
================================================================================

If you also want RAG on the single-stage path, add the same block to
match_buyers_for_intake(), after the result persistence loop and before
the return.  Same code, same placement.
